title: Why did Anička’s boots get wet? Slovak folk songs are quirky
itunes:author: The Slovak Spectator
itunes:summary:
Anna and Peter are inviting you to their listening party on this week’s Spectacular Slovakia. They will reveal just how many Slovak folk songs there are, but most importantly, they will play a few folk songs with whimsical lyrics. Can you help them fix a furnace that fell apart? 
 
A list of folk groups featured in the podcast by YouTube: Heľpan, Hradišťanka, Hromnica, Ištvánci, and Darinka & Milan Stingray. 
 
Photo: TASR
